# Copy this to your .env files and update with your actual Cloudinary values

# CLIENT .env file (client/.env)
REACT_APP_CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME=your-cloud-name
REACT_APP_CLOUDINARY_UPLOAD_PRESET=your-upload-preset

# Example values (replace with your actual values):
# REACT_APP_CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME=denhmcs4e
# REACT_APP_CLOUDINARY_UPLOAD_PRESET=lms_video_uploads

# How to get these values:
# 1. Sign up at https://cloudinary.com/
# 2. Cloud Name: Found on your dashboard home page
# 3. Upload Preset: Create one in Settings > Upload > Add upload preset
#    - Make it "Unsigned" for direct browser uploads
#    - Set resource type to "Video"
#    - Set max file size to 104857600 (100MB)

# After setting up:
# 1. Restart your development server
# 2. Test uploading a video larger than 8MB
# 3. Should work without 413 errors!
